Title: Higher bundle gerbes and cohomology classes in gauge theories

Authors: A.L. Carey, M.K. Murray and B.L. Wang

Comments: 16 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: J.Geom.Phys. 21 (1997) 183-197

The notion of a higher bundle gerbe is introduced to give a geometricrealization of the higher degree integral cohomology of certain manifolds. Weconsider examples using the infinite dimensional spaces arising in gaugetheories.